<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 01 at 4:25PM MST  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Band of Snow Across Southwest Montana...
As of 420 PM, a band of snow was drifting southeastward across
Southwest Montana. This band of snow has a history of producing
heavy snow, with visibility around a quarter mile at times.
Snowfall rates around an inch per hour will be possible underneath
this band. If you are able to, consider delaying travel to allow
this band of snow to pass southeastward.</description>
